commit 24fcdfe68560ccc5701cea797c3d02b0cc9814ac
Author: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date:   Sun Mar 1 19:40:06 2026 +0000

    feat: Brain API ΓÇö 8 domain brains replace 678 flat endpoints
    
    Instead of 678+ flat API routes, Grace now exposes 8 domain 'brains':
    
      POST /brain/chat     ΓÇö conversations, prompts, consensus, world model
      POST /brain/files    ΓÇö folders, documents, uploads, search, librarian
      POST /brain/govern   ΓÇö governance, approvals, rules, persona, genesis
      POST /brain/ai       ΓÇö consensus, models, coding agent, oracle, console
      POST /brain/system   ΓÇö health, diagnostics, runtime, triggers, probe
      POST /brain/data     ΓÇö whitelist sources, knowledge mining, flash cache
      POST /brain/tasks    ΓÇö scheduling, time sense, planner
      POST /brain/code     ΓÇö codebase, projects, version control, code gen
      GET  /brain/directory ΓÇö list all brains and their actions
    
    Usage: POST /brain/{domain} { action: 'send', payload: { message: 'hi' } }
    
    Each brain is a thin facade (~10-15 actions) that routes to existing
    internal services. Benefits:
      - 8 endpoints to probe instead of 678
      - 1 auth check per domain
      - Swap subsystems without client breakage
      - Every call tracked via Genesis key (brain + action level)
      - Clean BrainResponse: {brain, action, ok, data, error, latency_ms}
    
    Consensus opinion (Kimi + Opus):
      Kimi: 'Do it ΓÇö treat brains as thin versioned facades, not monoliths'
      Opus: 'Proceed ΓÇö add action schema discovery + standardized errors'
    
    Existing 678 routes remain for backward compatibility.
    
    Co-authored-by: aaron031291 <aaron031291@users.noreply.github.com>
